SECTION I — COMMON CLARIFICATIONS (no ambiguity)
────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
Q: Is there a universal age limit for Skilled Worker / Student visas? A: No. There is no universal statutory maximum age. Eligibility assessments focus on job, skill, funds, sponsor and genuine intent. :contentReference[oaicite:45]{index=45}

Q: Are specific monthly maintenance figures fixed nationwide? A: The Student route publishes specific monthly maintenance amounts based on where you study (London vs outside London). Use the official GOV.UK figures at application time. :contentReference[oaicite:46]{index=46}

Q: Does a high income in the home country guarantee a UK visa? A: No. Home-country income may support proof of funds but does not replace route-specific salary or funding tests (e.g., Skilled Worker salary requirement or Student maintenance). :contentReference[oaicite:47]{index=47}

